The paper deals with community detection in online social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of network characteristics and information from other aligned networks, which could fall under the sub-category of social computing (cs.SOC). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which could fall under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
